  "title": "Sales Manager (Marine and Offshore)",
  "description": "<h2><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></h2><ul><li><p>Drive business development for assigned product lines across domestic and international markets</p></li><li><p>Develop and execute sales strategies, business plans, and customer proposals to achieve sales targets and healthy margins</p></li><li><p>Prepare sales forecasts and monthly/annual sales plans</p></li><li><p>Conduct sales visits and expand market presence across marine, offshore, oil & gas, power generation, petrochemical, and industrial sectors</p></li><li><p>Build and maintain strong relationships with OEMs, principals, and suppliers for engines and machinery spare parts</p></li><li><p>Monitor market trends, competitor activities, and new or emerging technologies to support sales strategy</p></li><li><p>Support company growth by sharing product knowledge and providing coaching or training to sales team members when required</p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance with internal processes and ISO management systems</p></li></ul><h2><strong>Requirements</strong></h2><ul><li><p>Diploma or Degree in Engineering, Business, or a related discipline</p></li><li><p>Minimum 5 years of sales experience in <strong>engine or machinery spare parts</strong> within the marine, offshore, or oil & gas industry</p></li><li><p>Proficient in Microsoft Office</p></li><li><p>Strong commercial and negotiation skills with a results-driven mindset</p></li><li><p>Able to work independently, manage pressure, and maintain attention to detail</p></li><li><p>Continuous improvement and professional work attitude</p></li><li><p>Possess a valid Class 3 driving licence and willing to travel overseas when required</p></li></ul>",
